	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>My druid is equipped with 2 25hp/35mana rings, just like this item, but without the effect.<br>I love those earrings. When you are maxed out on wisdom, mana is the next best thing. Plus 50 hp is good too.<br>Now, I paid a bundle to get those earrings for my druid. Why? Because everyone can wear them.<br>This earring? I bought for 400pp, because it was mage only, and no one wanted it.<br>Fits nicely on my 8 mage.<br>Granted, he is not maxed out in int, but still, at level 8, 35 mana is really nice, and hp at that level can save you<br><br>Overall, I cant see why people dont look past the effect attached to an item.<br>For this item, any mage that has maxed int, and wants more mana, should look at this item.<br>Hell, I would have bought it if it had a level 1 spell attached to it.<br><br>Sglanton L'ostinato - 49 Druid<br>Trixare - 8 Magician<br>Torvonnlious<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
